<div id="c2">
<p>This problem is not as prevalent in more phonetic languages. My family and I were discussing this last weekend - in Russian, as soon as you learn the alphabet, you can read since you can just sound out the words one letter at a time, then say them faster, and in nearly every case, you&#8217;ll hear the word you just read.</p>

