<p>Pavel&#8217;s point is spot on.  English is an outlier among alphabetically encoded languages; for data on the effects of orthography on learning to read, see <em>Foundation literacy acquisition in European orthographies</em> &lt;www.psycho.univ-paris5.fr/IMG/pdf/2003_Seymour.pdf>.</p>

