<div id="c9">
<p>I work IT in a school system and Kurzweil 3000 does exactly this.</p>

<p>You basically scan in a textbook (or any printed matter) and it reads it back to the kids. They can repeat sentences, words, etc. as they need.</p>

<p>The teacher in charge swears by it for helping less developed and challenged students.</p>

<p>It&#8217;s also about $3K for the basic package.</p>

